Description:
A sanctuary of style & quality
Another successful marketing campaign by Team Newbond at Woodards Carnegie - considering selling call Cedric 0418 326 174 or Maria 0407 359 676 for exceptional service:
Architect-designed, master craftsmen-built and with an interior conceived by an award winning designer, this beautiful modern home is a reflection of the skill, love and care lavished upon it. It is the front of 2 on the block, with a real sense of privacy and peacefulness. Gleaming hardwood flooring and extensive glazing enhanced by superb presentation and an open, spacious, fresh, natural light-drenched interior make this residence shine. The L-shape lounge-dining room has door out to a deck and the pretty front garden. A chic kitchen (with Asko appliances) is open to the family room, leading to a private decked area. The master bedroom (WIR; shared access to a bathroom) is on the ground floor, zoned apart from 3 upstairs bedrooms (BIRs) which have pitched ceilings and are serviced by a large bathroom. Ducted heating and a double garage (automatic door) are among the inclusions. This prestigious property is in a prime pocket of Ormond with convenient access to the best Ormond, Carnegie and Glen Huntly offer.
Cedric Newbond : 0418 326 174

Description:
Californian Comfort With A McKinnon College Address
Enjoying a coveted location in the McKinnon Secondary College zone, this Californian Bungalow is captivating on the outside and beautifully proportioned on the inside. Richly textured with perfectly preserved period detail including leadlight, patterned ceilings and floorboards, the immaculately maintained home caters to an effortless family lifestyle with a formal living room, family/sitting room with a crackling wood fireplace, slate-tiled dining room, timber kitchen, three bedrooms (BIRs), lovely claw-foot bathroom, second toilet and a large laundry. A pull-down ladder leads to a large loft, which is easily adaptable into a study or dream kids' retreat - and you'll still have plenty of space for storage. A huge covered alfresco area with rear access is perfect for entertaining and relaxing outdoors in Melbourne's 'four-seasons-in-one-day' weather. Further features include alarm system and off-street parking for up to four cars. Ormond and McKinnon Stations, Allnutt Park, Kilvington Grammar and Ormond Primary School are all within easy reach.

Description:
Under Contract
This charming solid brick home awaits the renovator's magic touch! With a generous 582sqm there is ample room to redevelop or extend (STCA).
The possibilities are endless with a spacious lounge with room for formal dining, exposed timber beams, fully carpeted, ducted heating and ceiling fan.
Two bedrooms fully carpeted in soft pastel tones, ceiling fan with shared bathroom and an additional bedroom with ensuite.
The large kitchen in a timber finish has modern appliances, split unit air-conditioning and a meals area with access to the Alfresco entertaining area adjacent to an external laundry.
Also includes a double lock up garage and/or storage area.
Central located in the McKinnon school zone and a short walk to Joyce Park, Ormond train station, bus or the local North Road shops, cafes and restaurants.

Description:
Alluring charm in quiet convenience
A tranquil retreat at the rear of the block in the highly desirable McKinnon Secondary zone, this endlessly appealing owner built Federation style home simply glows with pride! Beyond a covered verandah with feature timber fretwork, the character continues inside where a generous, light filled lounge and dining is overlooked by the stunning, thoughtfully designed central timber kitchen enjoying tranquil garden vistas to the private paved north facing courtyard. With three bedrooms including generous master with walk in robe and ensuite, gleaming family bathroom featuring spa bath, shower and heated towel rail, large laundry with external access, excellent hallway storage, plus slab heating, split system heating and cooling, ducted vacuum, alarm, 12 solar panels, outdoor blinds, single remote garage with storage space and additional car parking - this outstanding home meets every criteria for total comfort and convenience.
Easy access to train & bus routes, beautiful parklands, bayside beaches, cafe precinct of McKinnon Rd village & shopping strips of Glenhuntly, North & Centre Roads.
Brad Hateley : 0412933883

Description:
Contemporary chic with a private courtyard
Make a statement about clever contemporary design and about a relaxing lifestyle when you buy this chic ground-floor apartment. It is private, peaceful and well located; it provides all the inclusions you want, and it is virtually no maintenance. Simply kickback and enjoy an open plan living room, flooded with sunlight, and with a rev-cyc A/C and an on-trend kitchen with glass splashback, stone benchtop and stainless steel appliances. Sliding doors open to a grassy, private courtyard that promises to be a delightful alfresco entertaining space. The 2 bedrooms have BIRs, with the master bedroom sharing access to the bathroom. There is also a European laundry, and a secure basement car park with storage cage. The convenience to Ormond shops, cafes, trains, buses, reserves and recreation is another reason to place this property at the top of your “must see” list.

Superbly positioned just moments to fantastic local amenities and attractions, and showing off with exceptional internal space, this two bedroom apartment on the first floor of this low-density Grange Road complex will be highly desired amongst first home buyers, smart investors, and everyone in between.
This fabulous retreat shows off with a generous central living and dining zone with a dedicated study space, while the polished timber floor entry leads its way to the terrific stone kitchen which enjoys quality stainless steel appliances. Placing the style in lifestyle
The distinctive contemporary design of the building is indicative of the stylish, natural light-flooded interior and the sophisticated lifestyle on offer in this first-floor apartment. Easy to maintain and easy to live in, this home has an open living room (with rev-cyc A/C) that
encompasses sitting area, dining space, study nook, and a sleek stone and stainless steel kitchen with breakfast bar. Sliding doors open to a private balcony. The two sizeable
bedrooms have built-in wardrobes and a restful ambience. There is an on-trend bathroom and separate powder room. Security is important here: video intercom entry and secure
basement car parking (plus storage cage) feature. The location is close to Ormond shops, cafes, trains and buses, near reserves, recreation, schools, and convenient to Monash Uni (Caulfield)

Description:
Low maintenance & well located
Secure with intercom entry and remote-controlled gates to the carport, this 1st floor apartment is at the front of the block in a location that is mere metres away from the North Road shops, eateries, trains and buses, close to parks, recreation and schools and with easy access to Monash Uni - Caulfield and Clayton campuses. Sunlight streams into the living room, which has a split system A/C. There's a separate easy-to-work-in kitchen; and both bedrooms have BIRs. Singles, couples, small families and investors will all be interested in this property!

Description:
Peaceful, sunny & well located
The northerly aspect means sunlight streams in the living room window of this appealing first-floor apartment. Set at the peaceful rear of the block, the home - ideal for investors or owner-occupiers - has a bright interior with feature parquetry flooring. The bathroom (with laundry facilities) is ensuite-style to the bedroom, which has twin built-in wardrobes. Gas hot water, gas cooking and a gas space heater are included. There's an undercover car park, and from here it's only metres to reserves, Ormond shops, cafes, trains and buses as well as recreation. There's also convenient access to both Monash University campuses.
